  "text": "In our modelling below, we consider the consequences of a slightly off-axis angular momentum flux. Specifically, we assume that the magnitude of the torque isL as defined above, but its direction makes an angle with the stellar spin axis, and is directed at an angle ψ when projected onto a plane normal to the stellar spin axis (see Figure 1 for a schematic). Both and ψ vary stochastically, as an Ornstein-Uhlenbeck process with autocorrelation time τ c , reflecting a random process that nevertheless exhibits some degree of \"memory\" over timescales of τ c [CITATION_1] 2 . The root-mean-square value of (or its standard deviation) is set equal to 0 whereas ψ is isotropically-varying.",
